LAUNCH POWERSHELL : powershell

DISPLAY FILE CONTENTS : get-content Filename

CHANGE DIRECTORY : set-location -path \Path\

LIST CMD LET, FUNCTIONS, SCRIPTS, ALIASES : get-command

LIST SPECIFIC COMMAND : get-command command-type "cmdlet" 

DETAILS ABOUT A CMDLET LIKE DATE : get-help get-date

COMMANDAS START WITH VERB REMOVE : Get-Command -Name Remove*

SEARCH ECHO ALIAS : Write-Output

EXAMPLE USAGE FOR CMDLET New-LocalUser : Get-Help New-LocalUser -examples


LIST FILE AND FOLDERS IN DIRECTORY : get-childitem \Path\

CREATE NEW FILE : new-item -path \path\ -itemtype "File"

CREATE NEW FOLDER : new-item -path \path\ -itemtype "Directory"

DELETE FILE OR FOLDER : remove-item -path \path\

COPYING OR MOVE ITEM : copy-item -path \Source_path\ -destination \-destination_path\


SORTING CONTENT BY LENGTH : get-childitem -path \Path\ | sort-object length

FILES ENDING WITH EXTENSION txt : Get-ChildItem | Where-Object -Property "Extension" -eq ".txt"

LIST NEEDFUL FILEDS : Get-ChildItem | Select-Object Name,Length 

SORTING AND FILTER LARGEST FILE : Get-ChildItem | Sort-Object Length -Descending | Select-Object -First 1

SEARCH KEYWORD : Select-String -Path \path\ -Pattern "keyword" 


GET COMPUTERS DETAILS : get-computerinfo

LIST LOCAL USER ACCOUNTS : get-localuser

NETWORK INTERFACE DETAILS : Get-NetIPConfiguration

DETAILS OF IPs : Get-NetIPAddress


DETAILED LIST OF RUNNING PROCESSES : Get-Process

GET STATUS OF ALL SERVICES : get-service

DETAILS OF ACTIVE CONNECTIONS : Get-NetTCPConnection

GENERATE FILE HASH : get-filehash -path \path\Filename

RUN COMMANDS ON LOCAL AND REMOTE COMPUTERS : get-help invoke-command -examples 

